            "body": "@seandewar how egregious would it be to just allow UI callbacks to edit text regardless of textlock? Can we just move the responsibility to not break Nvim on the UI?ðŸ˜‡ Are there situations where changing the text of dedicated UI buffers would lead to problems (I'm not sure I quite grasp which problems textlock is supposed to avoid in which situations).\n\nI.e. this patch \"resolves\" this issue, seemingly without problems:\n```diff\n@@ -744,6 +744,10 @@ void ui_call_event(char *name, bool fast, Array args)\n   bool handled = false;\n   UIEventCallback *event_cb;\n\n+  // UI callbacks need to be allowed to change text.\n+  int save_textlock = textlock;\n+  textlock = 0;\n...\n+  textlock = save_textlock;\n```",
