            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It's certainly naughty, but I can't think of a better solution right now ðŸ˜‡; extui ideally ought to work in situations where the old UI does.\n\nNo idea of the impact, but if it sticks to interacting with its own windows/buffers and doesn't switch windows/buffers (though temporarily may be fine), things may be fine?  \nIdeally it should also avoid opportunities where user code might run while `textlock` is bypassed.  \n(Also I wonder if `expr_map_locked` may likewise be relevant too?)\n\nIn any case, looks like #30246 has bravely [opened this Pandora's box](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/30246/files#diff-dc79dd239e890a1e64119798c8dd6c797624b5f9f55237cd0c41ad410ab56f04R814-R819) in some capacity anyway. ðŸ™ˆ ",
